The paper discusses a methodology for analyzing how Wikipedia editors regard science through their references to scientific papers. The method of co-citation has been adapted to this context in order to generate Pathfinder networks (PFNET) that highlight the most relevant scientific journals and categories, and their interactions in order to find out how scientific literature is consumed through this open encyclopaedia. This methodology involves techniques related to digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social networks (cs.SI), data mining (cs.SD), and cybernetics (cs.CY).
